article.description: — Cameron Krutwig had 18 points and five assists as Loyola of Chicago won its seventh straight game, romping past Missouri State 72-46 on Sunday.
article.headline: Krutwig leads Loyola of Chicago past Missouri St. 72-46
article.linkText: Krutwig leads Loyola of Chicago past Missouri St. 72-46
article.story: SPRINGFIELD, Mo. -- — Cameron Krutwig had 18 points and five assists as Loyola of Chicago won its seventh straight game, romping past Missouri State 72-46 on Sunday. Keith Clemons had 12 points and six rebounds for Loyola of Chicago (14-3, 9-1 Missouri Valley Conference). The Bears’ 27.1 field goal percentage represented the worst mark by a Loyola of Chicago opponent this season. Loyola of Chicago dominated the first half and led 41-16 at the break. The Bears’ 16 points in the first half marked a season low for the team. Isiaih Mosley had 8 points and 10 rebounds for the Bears (9-4, 5-4). Gaige Prim added eight rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC,
